headline: Tesla Stock Broke Out But This Longtime Bull Decided To Take Profit

headline: Tesla ramps up battery cell investments at German gigafactory
summary: Tesla is creating the conditions to produce up to 8 ​gigawatt hours of battery cells a year ‌at its German gigafactory in Gruenheide near Berlin starting ‌in 2027, the U.S. automaker said in a statement on Tuesday.  "To this end, we are investing another three-digit million amount in cell production," it ⁠said, adding this ‌would take total investments in the local cell factory to nearly 1 billion ‍euros ($1.2 billion).  The Gruenheide ⁠plant, which employs around 11,500 staff, is Tesla's only gigafactory in Europe, a market ⁠where the U.S. electric vehicle pioneer has faced dwindling ‌market share.

headline: The Electric Car Transition Unravels Slowly, Then All at Once
